        "benefits": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The components of the AMRUT consist of capacity building, reform implementation, water supply, sewerage and septage management, storm water drainage, urban transport and development of green spaces and parks. During the process of planning, the Urban Local Bodies (ULBs) will strive to include some smart features in the physical infrastructure components."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The details of the Mission components are given below."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Water Supply"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ol_list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Water supply systems including augmentation of existing water supply, water treatment plants and universal metering."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Rehabilitation of old water supply systems, including treatment plants."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Rejuvenation of water bodies specifically for drinking water supply and recharging of ground water."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Special water supply arrangement for difficult areas, hill and coastal cities, including those having water quality problems (e.g. arsenic, fluoride)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Sewerage"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ol_list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Decentralised, networked underground sewerage systems, including augmentation of existing sewerage systems and sewage treatment plants."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Rehabilitation of old sewerage system and treatment plants."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Recycling of water for beneficial purposes and reuse of wastewater."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Septage"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ol_list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Faecal Sludge Management- cleaning, transportation and treatment in a cost-effective manner."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mechanical and biological cleaning of sewers and septic tanks and recovery of operational cost in full."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Storm Water Drainage"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ol_list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Construction and improvement of drains and storm water drains in order to reduce and eliminate flooding."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "heading_four",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Urban Transport"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ol_list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Ferry vessels for inland waterways (excluding port/bay infrastructure) and buses."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Footpaths/walkways, sidewalks, foot over-bridges and facilities for non-motorised transport (e.g. bicycles)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list_item",
                "children": [
